377
00:27:56,129 --> 00:28:01,098
My brother-in-law,
my DEA agent brother-in-law?

378
00:28:01,425 --> 00:28:03,643
He's onto Gus.

379
00:28:09,390 --> 00:28:12,901
Did you hear what I just said?
My brother-in-law is onto Gus.

380
00:28:13,102 --> 00:28:17,277
Yeah, yeah, yeah, I got it,
your brother-in-law. Okay, I'm thinking.

381
00:28:20,608 --> 00:28:26,954
Look. So, what if this is
like math or algebra?

382
00:28:27,155 --> 00:28:31,461
We add a plus douche bag
to a minus douche bag...

383
00:28:31,659 --> 00:28:34,162
...and you get, like,
zero douche bags.

384
00:28:35,329 --> 00:28:37,548
I've got some math for you.

385
00:28:37,748 --> 00:28:41,341
Hank catching Gus
equals Hank catching us.

386
00:28:42,794 --> 00:28:47,053
Hank, he's relentless, all right?
He won't quit.

387
00:28:47,256 --> 00:28:50,304
Yeah, well, he's got nothing,
is all I can say.

388
00:28:50,509 --> 00:28:53,688
- How would you know that?
- Because he's still above ground.

389
00:28:53,887 --> 00:28:58,643
Think a dude like Gus would let
your boy anywhere near him?

390
00:28:58,849 --> 00:29:01,814
He'll break out his box cutter
on his sorry gimp ass.

391
00:29:02,853 --> 00:29:07,740
So you haven't even seen him
since that time at the diner?

392
00:29:12,319 --> 00:29:13,956
Okay.

393
00:29:16,823 --> 00:29:19,587
Think. All right.

394
00:29:24,204 --> 00:29:26,624
They've got to be figuring
that we've talked.

395
00:29:27,249 --> 00:29:31,887
So you need to tell Mike that you
are worried about Hank's investigation.

396
00:29:32,086 --> 00:29:35,432
Okay? Hank already knows
who you are, by the way.

397
00:29:35,631 --> 00:29:40,518
