But tell me something.

488
00:37:44,719 --> 00:37:47,103
That chicken, so fabulous...

489
00:37:48,055 --> 00:37:50,060
...so excellent...

490
00:37:50,390 --> 00:37:52,893
Besides that, what else
do you have on your menu?

491
00:37:53,852 --> 00:37:55,405
We have several side dishes.

492
00:37:55,853 --> 00:37:57,692
Rice. Beans.

493
00:37:58,147 --> 00:38:00,483
Sometimes we prepare
a carnitas entrée...

494
00:38:00,816 --> 00:38:03,496
...if we come across fresh beef
in the market.

495
00:38:04,819 --> 00:38:05,827
Anything else?

496
00:38:07,071 --> 00:38:08,494
Come on, be honest.

497
00:38:09,323 --> 00:38:13,463
There is nothing else you offer?
A little taste of something else?

498
00:38:13,660 --> 00:38:16,424
Something on the side?

499
00:38:17,247 --> 00:38:21,422
Because when I send my men
to your restaurant...

500
00:38:22,501 --> 00:38:25,715
...they come back
with more than just chicken.

501
00:38:26,296 --> 00:38:28,515
They come back with drugs.

502
00:38:30,592 --> 00:38:32,394
Regresan high.

503
00:38:34,178 --> 00:38:36,811
You are selling them narcotics.

504
00:38:37,097 --> 00:38:39,814
Methamphetamine.

505
00:38:42,101 --> 00:38:44,106
With all due respect, Don Eladio.

506
00:38:44,312 --> 00:38:45,818
I didn't sell it to them.

507
00:38:46,021 --> 00:38:47,824
I gave them samples.

508
00:38:48,816 --> 00:38:50,239
Samples.

509
00:38:52,235 --> 00:38:54,655
Some businessman.

510
00:38:55,279 --> 00:38:58,411
I gave them samples to give to you.

511
00:38:59,867 --> 00:39:01,622
To introduce you to our product.

512
00:39:01,910 --> 00:39:03,962
Don Eladio, Gustavo meant no offense.

513
00:39:04,454 --> 00:39:07,218
But he...that is to say we...

514
00:39:07,498 --> 00:39:10,463
...could think of no other way
to get your attention.

515
00:39:11,669 --> 00:39:13,720
We want to work with you, Don Eladio.

516
00:39:15,046 --> 00:39:18,474
I know all about methamphetamine.

517
00:39:21,052 --> 00:39:24,230
That's poor man's cocaine.

518
00:39:25,806 --> 00:39:31,108
Only bikers and hillbillies use it.

519
00:39:32,353 --> 00:39:35,152
There's no money in it.

520
00:39:35,606 --> 00:39:37,029
May I, Don Eladio ...

521
00:39:37,441 --> 00:39:39,446
I am a biochemist by training.

522
00:39:39,693 --> 00:39:42,196
The methamphetamine we make
is much superior...

523
00:39:42,487 --> 00:39:45,701
...to the so-called biker crank
you know of.

524
00:39:46,073 --> 00:39:47,663
It is crystallized, like glass.

525
00:39:48,242 --> 00:39:49,250
Purer.

526
00:39:49,451 --> 00:39:51,586
And the chirality of the molecule...

527
00:39:51,786 --> 00:39:54,123
...its very structure, is different.

528
00:39:54,330 --> 00:39:56,252
The narcotic effect is far more potent.

529
00:39:56,541 --> 00:39:59,589
This product is the drug of the future.

530
00:40:00,711 --> 00:40:02,550
It'll triple your profits.

531
00:40:03,713 --> 00:40:04,840
Perhaps quadruple.

532
00:40:06,758 --> 00:40:08,727
They're not only good cooks...

533
00:40:08,926 --> 00:40:10,896
...they're great at shoveling manure.

534
00:40:18,768 --> 00:40:22,315
Right now, you deal almost exclusively
with cocaine.

535
00:40:22,605 --> 00:40:24,609
But the coca plant can't grow
in Mexico.

536
00:40:25,357 --> 00:40:27,860
You are no more than middlemen...

537
00:40:28,068 --> 00:40:30,037
...for the Colombians.

538
00:40:30,528 --> 00:40:34,787
They cut you a percentage for
smuggling across the border.

539
00:40:37,284 --> 00:40:40,914
But the lion's share
of the profits goes to them...

540
00:40:42,038 --> 00:40:45,917
...despite your assumption
of all the risk.

541
00:40:46,709 --> 00:40:48,678
This new crystal methamphetamine ...

542
00:40:48,877 --> 00:40:53,765
it's stronger,
more addictive than cocaine...

543
00:40:54,340 --> 00:40:57,353
...which means
it will move in higher volume.

544
00:40:57,551 --> 00:41:00,516
But most importantly,
it's completely artificial.

545
00:41:00,929 --> 00:41:03,016
We can show you
how to manufacture it...

546
00:41:03,223 --> 00:41:04,350
...right here in Mexico.

547
00:41:05,100 --> 00:41:07,780
And you keep all the profits.

548
00:41:11,563 --> 00:41:14,576
My men do like your product.

549
00:41:17,986 --> 00:41:21,200
Hector, what is wrong with you?

550
00:41:21,405 --> 00:41:24,833
Why did you not get glasses
for our guests?

551
00:41:25,951 --> 00:41:27,920
Go on.

552
00:41:32,123 --> 00:41:35,136
You are quite the talent.

553
00:41:36,001 --> 00:41:40,177
I bet you learned cooking
from your mama. isn't that true?

554
00:41:41,381 --> 00:41:46,185
But...what about the chemistry?

555
00:41:46,927 --> 00:41:49,477
I studied at the University of Santiago.

556
00:41:49,721 --> 00:41:51,892
Gustavo paid for my education.

557
00:41:52,098 --> 00:41:53,142
Oh, really?

558
00:41:53,975 --> 00:41:59,028
I have degrees in both biochemistry
and chemical engineering.

559
00:41:59,396 --> 00:42:01,697
With minimal capital investment...

560
00:42:01,940 --> 00:42:04,324
...we can set up
a factory-grade laboratory for you.

561
00:42:04,526 --> 00:42:07,740
Train your own people
to manufacture large quantities...

562
00:42:07,945 --> 00:42:09,784
...of highly pure methamphetamine.

563
00:42:11,240 --> 00:42:12,248
Fantastic!

564
00:42:16,328 --> 00:42:17,620
Tell me one thing, though.

565
00:42:18,246 --> 00:42:20,298
If you're the cook ...

566
00:42:20,498 --> 00:42:22,633
Why do I need him?

567
00:42:25,502 --> 00:42:26,594
Señor?

568
00:42:27,921 --> 00:42:29,048
You.

569
00:42:29,255 --> 00:42:30,809
Businessman.

570
00:42:31,007 --> 00:42:35,894
Why should I negotiate with someone
who doesn't respect me?

571
00:42:36,887 --> 00:42:41,477
Who insults me by dealing
under my nose without my permission?

572
00:42:42,517 --> 00:42:45,530
Who manipulates me into a meeting...

573
00:42:47,229 --> 00:42:49,115
...in front of my own men?

574
00:42:50,232 --> 00:42:52,533
What do I need you for?

575
00:42:54,527 --> 00:42:56,247
Don Eladio. Please.

576
00:42:56,445 --> 00:42:58,082
I didn't sell anything.

577
00:42:58,364 --> 00:43:00,451
I apologise if you are offended...

578
00:43:00,657 --> 00:43:03,836
...by my method
of obtaining this meeting.

579
00:43:04,202 --> 00:43:07,416
I merely took the initiative.

580
00:43:08,456 --> 00:43:12,417
I meant no insult.

581
00:43:12,876 --> 00:43:14,798
Don Eladio,
Gustavo didn't mean to offend.

582
00:43:15,128 --> 00:43:16,682
I know Gustavo like a brother.

583
00:43:16,880 --> 00:43:18,172
He's an honorable man.

584
00:43:18,381 --> 00:43:21,098
The most loyal man I have ever known.

585
00:43:21,550 --> 00:43:23,555
He rescued me
from the Santiago slums.

586
00:43:23,761 --> 00:43:25,350
He made me the man I am today!

587
00:43:25,971 --> 00:43:28,307
Gustavo is a genius.
He will make you millions!

588
00:43:28,765 --> 00:43:32,027
Just find it in your heart to forgive him
this one small mistake.

589
00:43:32,893 --> 00:43:33,902
Please...

590
00:43:35,688 --> 00:43:36,696
He's my partner.

591
00:43:37,105 --> 00:43:39,656
I need him! I swear to God!

592
00:44:16,139 --> 00:44:17,147
Look at him.

593
00:44:17,348 --> 00:44:18,855
You did this to him.

594
00:44:19,725 --> 00:44:22,904
Now, look at him.

595
00:44:36,740 --> 00:44:38,211
Listen to me.

596
00:44:38,909 --> 00:44:43,499
The only reason you are alive
and he is not...

597
00:44:44,747 --> 00:44:48,009
...is because I know who you are.

598
00:44:48,792 --> 00:44:49,884
But understand ...

599
00:44:50,585 --> 00:44:52,555
You are not in Chile any more.

600
00:45:04,889 --> 00:45:06,147
My advice ...

601
00:45:07,558 --> 00:45:09,444
Stick to chicken.

602
00:45:46,675 --> 00:45:48,597
Look at me, Hector.

603
00:45:54,849 --> 00:45:59,404
Look at me.

604
00:46:21,455 --> 00:46:23,460
Maybe next time.

